Section 1:
1 L.D. 1727
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Clerk of the House.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1154, L.D. 1727, “An Act to Ensure
10 Transparency in Consumer Transactions Involving Artificial Intelligence”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 10 MRSA c. 239 is enacted to read:
14 CHAPTER 239
15 COMMUNICATIONS WITH CONSUMERS VIA ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE
16 §1500-Y. Required disclosure of use of artificial intelligence chatbot to engage in trade
17 and commerce
18 1. Definitions. As used in this section, unless the context otherwise indicates, the
19 following terms have the following meanings.
20 A. "Artificial intelligence chatbot" means a software application, web interface or
21 computer program that simulates human conversation and interaction through textual
22 or aural communications.
23 B. "Trade" and "commerce" have the same meaning as in Title 5, section 206,
24 subsection 3.
25 2. Required disclosure of use of artificial intelligence chatbot to engage in trade
26 and commerce. A person may not use an artificial intelligence chatbot or any other
27 computer technology to engage in trade and commerce with a consumer in a manner that
28 may mislead or deceive a reasonable consumer into believing that the consumer is engaging
29 with a human being unless the consumer is notified in a clear and conspicuous manner that
30 the consumer is not engaging with a human being.
31 3. Violation. A violation of subsection 2 is a violation of the Maine Unfair Trade
32 Practices Act.'
Page 1 - 132LR2313(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1154, L.D. 1727
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment prohibits a person from using an
55 artificial intelligence chatbot to engage in trade or commerce with a consumer in a manner
66 that may mislead or deceive a reasonable consumer into believing that the consumer is
77 engaging with a human being unless the consumer is notified that the consumer is not
88 engaging with a human being. The amendment also clarifies the language used in the bill
99 to be consistent with language used in the Maine Unfair Trade Practices Act.
1100 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1111 (See attached)
